Question

Match the following equations to their graphs.

  1. \(y=\frac{x \left(x + 4\right)}{4}\)
  2. \(y=5 \left(x - 6\right) \left(x - 4\right)\)
  3. \(y=\frac{\left(x - 8\right) \left(x - 2\right)}{9}\)
  4. \(y=\frac{4 \left(x + 1\right) \left(x + 8\right)}{7}\)

##ANSWER1##

##ANSWER2##

##ANSWER3##

##ANSWER4##

Answerlist

  • y=x*(x + 4)/4

  • y=5*(x - 6)*(x - 4)

  • y=(x - 8)*(x - 2)/9

  • y=4*(x + 1)*(x + 8)/7

  • y=x*(x + 4)/4

  • y=5*(x - 6)*(x - 4)

  • y=(x - 8)*(x - 2)/9

  • y=4*(x + 1)*(x + 8)/7

  • y=x*(x + 4)/4

  • y=5*(x - 6)*(x - 4)

  • y=(x - 8)*(x - 2)/9

  • y=4*(x + 1)*(x + 8)/7

  • y=x*(x + 4)/4

  • y=5*(x - 6)*(x - 4)

  • y=(x - 8)*(x - 2)/9

  • y=4*(x + 1)*(x + 8)/7

Solution

  1. The first graph has roots at 6 and 4. Notice the equation \(5 \left(x - 6\right) \left(x - 4\right)\) has factors that match those roots. Also, notice the parabola faces upward, and the expression has a positve multiplicative coefficient.
  2. The second graph has roots at -4 and 0. Notice the equation \(\frac{x \left(x + 4\right)}{4}\) has factors that match those roots. Also, notice the parabola faces upward, and the expression has a positve multiplicative coefficient.
  3. The third graph has roots at -8 and -1. Notice the equation \(\frac{4 \left(x + 1\right) \left(x + 8\right)}{7}\) has factors that match those roots. Also, notice the parabola faces upward, and the expression has a positve multiplicative coefficient.
  4. The fourth graph has roots at 8 and 2. Notice the equation \(\frac{\left(x - 8\right) \left(x - 2\right)}{9}\) has factors that match those roots. Also, notice the parabola faces upward, and the expression has a positve multiplicative coefficient.
